==English==

===Etymology===
From Spanish, past participle of [[aficionar]], ''to [[inspire]] [[affection]]'', from [[afición]], ''[[affection]]'', from {{L.}} [[affectio]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A person who likes, knows about, and appreciates a particular interest or activity; a [[fan]] or [[devotee]].
#:''Wiktionary is filled with '''aficionados''' of language and etymology.''

====Synonyms====
*(''one who likes, knows about, and appreciates something''): [[admirer]], [[buff]], [[enthusiast]], [[expert]],  [[follower]], [[lover]]

